T. J. Thyne https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/T._J._Thyne 0 Thomas Joseph "T.J." Thyne (born March 7, 1975) is an American actor, best known for his role in Bones as Dr. Jack Hodgins, an entomologist, mineralogist, and botanist. Thyne attended East Ridge Middle School in Ridgefield, Connecticut, before moving south to attend high school in Plano, Texas. He went on to attend the USC School of Dramatic Arts, graduating in 1997. In 2001, he co-founded Theatre Junkies, a group offering workshops and professional development for actors in the Greater Los Angeles Area.
